{
  "texts": [
    "In practice, they are given as a joint course over the course of two months in the fall semester.",
    "In this paper, \"the course\" thus refers to the joint course with students from both programs.",
    "As with other education at the graduate level in this university, the language of instruction is English.The goal of the course is for students to develop a set of professional competencies needed to succeed in their master's-level studies and potential professional careers in the particular context of Sweden.",
    "Thus, international students from several continents enroll and the syllabus is very diverse, touching upon many different topics, including:• Preparation for defending a master's thesis: academic writing (with L A T E X) and presentations,• Ethics in computing, • Equal opportunities (in other contexts known as DEIA: Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Access) in computing and in the Swedish context/legislation, • Academic honesty, • Introduction to C programming, • Project work with Raspberry Pi, etc.Different assignments throughout the course assess these various topics.",
    "As the course grade is pass or fail, all assignments are only graded as pass or fail, and all assignments (with opportunities for re-submission after feedback) must be passed to pass the course."
  ]
}